module.name: computer resources
module.description: A module that describes the available computer resources: Hard disk space, memory, CPU utilization, and CPU temperature.

embeddings.text: Check the CPU utilization using a command-line tool.
Monitor the memory usage of a running application.
Verify the available disk space on a specific drive.
Determine the number of open network connections for a process.
Evaluate the network bandwidth between two servers using a network testing tool.
Test the read and write speeds of a hard drive or SSD.
Inspect the network traffic of a specific port using a packet capture tool.
Determine the latency between two endpoints using a network testing tool.
Analyze the resource usage of a web application using a performance monitoring tool.
Check the number of threads running in a specific process.
Identify the processes consuming the most CPU resources.
Determine the network usage of a specific process or application.
Inspect the resource utilization of a virtual machine or container.
Monitor the temperature and fan speed of a CPU using a hardware monitoring tool.
Check the available RAM on a server or workstation.
Analyze the disk I/O operations of a running process.
Test the responsiveness of a website or web application using a load testing tool.
Determine the amount of CPU time used by a specific process.
Inspect the system logs for errors related to hardware resources.
Monitor the power usage of a system or server using a power management tool.
